    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-24T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winslow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-24T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received April 24—9:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Buero as head of Uruguayan delegation to the Preparatory Disarmament
                    Commission having received directly from the Secretariat of the League a copy of
                    my letter of April 8th to Drummond<note n="93" xml:id="d74fn93">See telegram No.
                        54, Apr. 7, 1926, to the Chargé in Switzerland, <ref target="#pg_70">p.
                            70</ref>.</note> told me at a private interview in his opinion the
                    attitude of the Department was entirely correct and that he could be counted on
                    to <pb facs="0233" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/> do all in his power to support our
                    views with regard to the organization of the work of the Conference when it
                    meets.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
